## Functions of the packages CredInd

The package `CredInd` has 3 functions that

\begin{itemize}
\item Read/manipulate (\textbf{ReadData}) the data;
\end{itemize}
```{r, eval=FALSE}
data1 <- ReadData(Indicator='Interest rate',
                  Index='Total')
```
\begin{itemize}
\vspace{-0.5cm}
\item Fit ARIMA models (\textbf{FitModels}); and
\end{itemize}
```{r, eval=FALSE}
model <- FitModels(data = data1, horizon=20)
```
\begin{itemize}
\vspace{-0.5cm}
\item Generate a plot (\textbf{plot\_FitModels}) for the selected credit indicator.
\end{itemize}
```{r, eval=FALSE}
plot_FitModels(model)
```

## Functions of the packages CredInd
When Indicator equals to 
```{r, eval=FALSE}
ReadData(Indicator='Interest rate', Index='Total')
```
\begin{itemize}
 \vspace{-0.35cm}
\item \textbf{Allowance}, the parameter Index can be Total, Public banks, National private control, Foreign control and Private control;
 \vspace{0.25cm}
\item \textbf{Spread} and \textbf{Interest rate}, Index can be Total, New operations companies, New operations households, Non-revolving total, Non-revolving companies and Non-revolving households;
 \vspace{0.25cm}
\item \textbf{Household debt}, Index can be Total and Without mortgage.
\vspace{0.25cm}
\end{itemize}

## Example
```{r, eval=FALSE}
data1 <- ReadData(Indicator = 'Interest rate',
                  Index = 'Total')
model1 <- FitModels(data = data1, horizon=20)
plot_FitModels(model1)
```
- Best model: ARIMA$(p=1,d=1,q=3)$, where $p$ is the AR order, $d$ is the degree of differencing and $m$ is the MA order;
- Correlation: $98\%$.

